description.p:
The virtual fab 300 enables interaction among the entities 302, 304 for purposes related to IC manufacturing, as well as the provision of services. In the present example, IC manufacturing can include one or more of the following steps:





receiving or modifying a customer's IC order of price, delivery, and/or quantity;

receiving or modifying an IC design;

receiving or modifying a process flow;

receiving or modifying a circuit design;

receiving or modifying a mask change;

receiving or modifying testing parameters;

receiving or modifying assembly parameters; and

receiving or modifying shipping of the ICs.

claim.claim-text:
1. A method for using a plurality of virtual backup service paths to dynamically switch between storage devices based on a plurality of backup scenarios, the method comprising:
defining a plurality of backup service groups containing at least one client;
defining a plurality of scenarios that each reference at least one virtual backup service path, wherein each virtual backup service path is defined by at least one network address identifying one of the storage devices;
determining which scenario of the plurality of scenarios is applicable based on a service level of the storage devices;
selecting the virtual backup service path identified by the applicable scenario;
receiving a request from one of the backup service groups to backup the at least one client; and
responding to the request with the selected virtual backup service path.

2. A method for dynamically switching to a second storage device when a service level of a first storage device indicates that the first storage device cannot be used, wherein the first and second storage devices are identified on a network by first and second network identifiers, respectively, the method comprising:
receiving a request from a first service group having a backup name, wherein the request is for a network identifier currently assigned to the backup name;
determining whether the first storage device can be used based on the service level of the first storage device, wherein the first network identifier is currently assigned to the backup name;
assigning the second network identifier to the backup name if the first storage device cannot be used;
responding to the request with the first network identifier if the first network identifier is currently assigned to the backup name or with the second network identifier if the second network identifier is currently assigned to the backup name;
assigning a priority level to the first service group;
determining whether the priority level of the first service group is higher than the priority level of a second service group that has issued a backup request; and
if the priority level of the first service group is higher, storing the data of the first service group before storing the data of the second service group.

3. A method for dynamically switching to a second storage device when a service level of a first storage device indicates that the first storage device cannot be used, wherein the first and second storage devices are identified on a network by first and second network identifiers, respectively, the method comprising:
receiving a request from a first service group having a backup name, wherein the request is for a network identifier currently assigned to the backup name;
determining whether the first storage device can be used based on the service level of the first storage device, wherein the first network identifier is currently assigned to the backup name;
assigning the second network identifier to the backup name if the first storage device cannot be used;
responding to the request with the first network identifier if the first network identifier is currently assigned to the backup name or with the second network identifier if the second network identifier is currently assigned to the backup name; and
prior to assigning the second network identifier to the backup name, determining if a service level of the second storage device indicates that the second storage device can be used.

4. A system for dynamically switching between storage devices, the system comprising:
a first and a second storage device identified by a first and a second network identifier, respectively, and associated with first and second service levels, respectively;
a service group associated with a backup name;
a name server adapted to maintain a name table pairing the backup name with the first or second network identifier;
first and second scenarios, wherein the first scenario pairs the backup name with the first network identifier if the first service level indicates that the first storage device can be used, and wherein the second scenario pairs the backup name with the second network identifier if the first service level indicates that the first storage device cannot be used; and
a plurality of instructions stored in a storage medium for execution by the system, the instructions including:
instructions for receiving a request from the service group for a network identifier associated with the backup name;
instructions for determining which of the first and second scenarios is applicable based on at least the first service level; and
instructions for responding to the request by providing the first or second network identifier identified by the applicable scenario.

9. A method for selecting a virtual backup service path for at least one service group having information to be stored, the method comprising:
monitoring a status of a plurality of storage devices;
determining that a change has occurred in the status of at least one of the storage devices;
selecting a scenario from a plurality of scenarios based on the status change, wherein each scenario defines a virtual service path identifying at least one of the storage devices for storing the information from the service group; and
updating a backup table based on the selected scenario, wherein the backup table associates the service group with the virtual service path defined by the selected scenario.

15. A system for monitoring a plurality of storage devices to determine a virtual backup service path for at least one service group having information to be stored, the system comprising:
a resource monitor adapted to monitor a status of at least some of the plurality of storage devices;
a plurality of scenarios, wherein each scenario corresponds to a status of the storage devices and defines a virtual service path;
a backup table adapted to associate the service group with the virtual service path of one of the plurality of scenarios; and
a plurality of instructions stored in a storage medium including:
instructions for receiving the status from the resource monitor;
instructions for identifying the scenario corresponding to the received status; and instructions for updating the backup table to associate the service group with the virtual service path of the corresponding scenario.
